    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="seven columns alpha">
        <h3><i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i> When does this ship out and when does it arrive?</h3>
        <p>We have a new issue of The Roasters Pack for every month. We mail out so that the coffee will be in your hands the first week of the month! Take a look at the timer above to know when we mail out our shipments.</p>
        <h3><i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i> Which coffees will I receive?</h3>
        <p>You will receive 3 delicious coffees from 3 different roasters. The coffees are a surprise so your palate will be taken on a coffee adventure with each issue. For examples of the coffee that has been featured previously, click <a href="http://instagram.com/p/p_sFNmSIgH/" target="_blank" title="Instagram July Issue of The Roasters Pack">here</a> or <a href="http://instagram.com/p/o0_Qa2SIg1" target="_blank" title="Instagram June Issue of The Roasters Pack">here</a> or check out our <a href="http://theroasterspack.com/collections/buy-canadian-coffee" title="Buy Canadian Coffee from The Roasters Pack">coffee store</a>!</p>
        <h3><i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i> How do you choose which coffees to put in The Roasters Pack?</h3>
        <p>We evaluate a tonne of coffees every month for a variety of factors – the body, acidity, finish, complexity, aftertaste and tasting notes. We want you to be able to discover the best coffees available and we sift through the masses to discover the ones that are incredibly exceptional.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="seven columns offset-by-one omega">
        <h3><i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i> How much coffee do I receive?</h3>
        <p>You will receive four ounces of three different roasts, to equal a total of 12 ounces. This makes over 35 cups of coffee!</p>
        <h3><i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i> How large is the package? Does it fit in my mailbox?</h3>
        <p>The package is 9 inches by 6.75 inches by 2.75 inches. If you’re Canadian, you’ll most likely receive a key for additional parcel compartments at the bottom of the community mailbox.</p>
        <h3><i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i> Where do you ship to?</h3>
        <p>Currently we ship to Canada &amp; USA. The shipping and tax is included, so the price you see is what you get!</p>
        <h3><i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i> How fresh is the coffee?</h3>
        <p>When we ship it out, it will be 1 to 7 days off of roast date. Our goal is to send you the freshest coffee as possible!</p>
    </div>
